description.narrative: Improved policies, processes, coordination mechanisms and capacities are in place to support the basic social-protection system through which Government-owned and managed social-protection programmes will be delivered post-2020., which contributes to Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, more children receive assistance through pilot social-protection programmes designed to enable all children to fully participate in the social and economic development of the nation and reach their full potential.
